Garage-to-ADU Conversion Roadmap: Portland 20261. Division of ResponsibilitiesTaskContractor (Halli Construction)OwnerPermit SubmittalProvides all technical plans (Site, Floor, Structural).Acts as the Applicant; uploads all documents to DevHub.Building WorkPerforms all structural framing, window installation, and shell.N/ATrade PermitsConsulting on code-compliant layout & circuit loads.Pulls Electrical, Plumbing, and Mechanical permits.Trade WorkN/APerforms all electrical, plumbing, and HVAC installation.InspectionsCoordinates and attends structural inspections.Schedules and attends all Electrical/Plumbing inspections.2. Mandatory Forms & Direct LinksPlease download and print these for the application packet.Residential Combination ApplicationThe primary application that bundles building, electric, and plumbing into one project.Owner Doing Work StatementCrucial: Required by Oregon law for you to perform your own trade work.SDC Waiver & CovenantWaives ~$10k–$20k in city fees. Note: Requires a Notary signature.Oregon Energy Code Selection (Measure A)Declares the insulation and window efficiency levels for the conversion.Simple Site Plan Erosion ControlRequired if we are trenching for new sewer, water, or power lines.3. Estimated City Fees (Portland 2026)Final fees are calculated by the city and paid via the DevHub portal.Building Permit & Plan Review: ~$1,500 – $2,500 (Varies by project valuation).Electrical Permit (Owner-Builder): ~$165 (Includes 200A service and branch circuits).Plumbing Permit (Owner-Builder): ~$350 – $500 (Based on number of fixtures).Mechanical Permit (Owner-Builder): ~$150 – $250 (For a ductless mini-split).System Development Charges (SDCs): $0 (If the SDC Waiver is signed and recorded).4. Key 2026 Regulatory NotesResidency Requirement: Per ORS 479.540, a homeowner can only perform their own electrical and plumbing if they own the home and intend to reside in the unit. Because you will be living in the ADU, you are legally permitted to do this.Egress Compliance: Sleeping areas must have at least one window with a clear opening of 5.7 sq. ft. and a sill height no higher than 44 inches from the floor.Fire Separation: If the garage is within 3 feet of the property line, the interior wall must be upgraded to a 1-hour fire-rated assembly.
